                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.283H3/126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-10T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 10, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 10—1:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. In the event of war between Great Britain and France for which preparations
                    are being made, our two British clerks are apprehensive of internment. I shall
                    resist such a measure on the ground of our extraterritoriality in accordance
                    with the views of Mr. Blake.<note n="38" xml:id="d746fn38">Maxwell Blake,
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier.</note> But I should
                    appreciate instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
